The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for real-time learning, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The algorithm also involves parameter optimization, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the algorithm for tasks such as handwritten digit recognition and multiplication table memorization, which are applications of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of symbols and memory in the multiplication table memorization task may also relate to the sub-category of structured data (cs.SD). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the algorithm for image recognition, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
